% ─── VARIABLES AND OPERATORS ──────────────────────────────────────────────

@label variables
    Variables are (not) set in cursive based on the \cmd{setmathitalic}
    setting. Standard arithmetic operators get proper implicit spacing.
    Explicit spacing can be add using standard TeX commands:

    $$ a + b - c $$
    $$ a \times b \div c $$
    $$ a \cdot b $$
    $$ \pm x \quad \mp y $$
@end

@cassilda: variables
│  Variables  are  (not)  set  in  cursive  based on the  \𝑠𝑒𝑡𝑚𝑎𝑡ℎ𝑖𝑡𝑎𝑙𝑖𝑐 setting.
│  Standard  arithmetic operators get proper  implicit spacing. Explicit  spacing
│  can be add using standard TeX commands:
│  
│                                    𝑎 + 𝑏 − 𝑐
│  
│                                    𝑎 × 𝑏 ÷ 𝑐
│  
│                                      𝑎 ⋅ 𝑏
│  
│                                    ±𝑥     ∓ 𝑦

% ─── SUPERSCRIPTS AND SUBSCRIPTS ─────────────────────────────────────────

@label scripts
    A caret ^ makes a superscript.  An underscore _ makes a
    subscript.  Use braces for multi-character exponents:

    $$ x^2, \quad x_i, \quad x_i^2, \quad x^{n+1}, \quad x_{i,j}, \quad a^{b^c} $$
@end

@cassilda: scripts
│  A  caret ^ makes a superscript. An underscore _ makes a subscript.  Use braces
│  for multi-character exponents:
│  
│                                                                 𝑐
│                 2               2       𝑛 + 1                  𝑏
│                𝑥 ,     𝑥 ,     𝑥 ,     𝑥     ,     𝑥    ,     𝑎
│                         𝑖       𝑖                   𝑖, 𝑗

% ─── SUBSCRIPT BRACING ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

@label subscript_bracing
    Subscripts and superscripts grab the next single token.
    Use braces for multi-token expressions like $x^{n+1}$
    or $a_{i,j}$.

    Commands that take arguments work without extra braces,
    just like in TeX. These are equivalent:

    $$ x_\mathbf{v} \quad x_{\mathbf{v}} \quad y^\hat{a} \quad y^{\hat{a}} $$

    More examples:

    $$ a_{i+1} \quad b^{n+1} \quad x_\text{max} $$
@end

@cassilda: subscript_bracing
