% ─── FLOOR AND CEILING ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

@label floor_ceil
    \cmd{lfloor}/\cmd{rfloor} make floor brackets.
    \cmd{lceil}/\cmd{rceil} make ceiling brackets.
    Both scale with \cmd{left}/\cmd{right}:
   
    $$ \lfloor x \rfloor $$
    $$ \lceil x \rceil $$
    $$ \left\lfloor \frac{x}{2} \right\rfloor $$
    $$ \left\lceil \frac{x}{2} \right\rceil $$
@end

@cassilda: floor_ceil
│  \𝑙𝑓𝑙𝑜𝑜𝑟/\𝑟𝑓𝑙𝑜𝑜𝑟 make floor brackets. \𝑙𝑐𝑒𝑖𝑙/\𝑟𝑐𝑒𝑖𝑙 make ceiling brackets. Both
│  scale with \𝑙𝑒𝑓𝑡/\𝑟𝑖𝑔ℎ𝑡:
│  
│                                       ⌊𝑥⌋
│  
│                                       ⌈𝑥⌉
│  
│                                     │  𝑥  │
│                                     │ ─── │
│                                     └  2  ┘
│  
│                                     ┌  𝑥  ┐
│                                     │ ─── │
│                                     │  2  │

% ─── GREEK LETTERS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@label greek
    Greek letters use backslash-name notation.  Lowercase:

    $$ \alpha \beta \gamma \delta \epsilon \zeta \eta \theta $$
    $$ \lambda \mu \nu \xi \pi \rho \sigma \tau $$
    $$ \phi \varphi \chi \psi \omega $$

    Uppercase (only for letters that differ from Latin):

    $$ \Gamma \Delta \Theta \Lambda \Xi \Pi \Sigma \Phi \Psi \Omega $$
@end

