│  
│                                 𝑎≢𝑏    𝐴⊄𝐵    ∄𝑥

% ─── DEFINITION SYMBOLS ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

@label definitions
    Definition symbols use relation spacing (space on both sides).
    The \cmd{coloneqq} command renders the Unicode ≔ symbol.
    The bare \verb|:=| is also recognized as a combined relation:

    $$ \Phi := S $$
    $$ f \coloneqq x^2 + 1 $$
    $$ g \eqqcolon h $$

    A bare colon is punctuation (no space before, space after),
    useful in set-builder notation:

    $$ \{x : x > 0\} $$
@end

@cassilda: definitions
│  Definition  symbols use relation spacing (space on both sides). The  \𝑐𝑜𝑙𝑜𝑛𝑒𝑞𝑞
│  command renders the Unicode ≔ symbol. The bare := is also  recognized as a co-
│  mbined relation:
│  
│                                      Φ ≔ 𝑆
│  
│                                         2
│                                    𝑓 ≔ 𝑥  + 1
│  
│                                      𝑔 ≕ ℎ
│  
│  A bare colon is punctuation (no space before, space after), useful in set-bui-
│  lder notation:
│  
│                                    {𝑥: 𝑥 > 0}

% ─── SET THEORY ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@label sets
    Membership, subset, union, intersection:

    $$ x \in A $$
    $$ x \notin A $$
    $$ A \subset B $$
    $$ A \subseteq B $$
    $$ A \cup B $$
    $$ A \cap B $$
    $$ A \setminus B $$
    $$ \emptyset $$
@end

