% ─── STANDARD FUNCTIONS ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

@label functions
    Standard functions are set in upright (roman) type.  Hyades
    recognises the usual names:

    $$ \sin x \quad \cos(x) \quad \tan x $$
    $$ \arcsin(x) \quad \arccos x \quad \arctan x $$
    $$ \sinh x \quad \cosh x \quad \tanh\left(\frac{x}{2}\right) $$
    $$ \log x \quad \log_2 x \quad \ln x \quad \exp(x) $$

    Functions can take powers:

    $$ \sin^2 x + \cos^2 x = 1 $$
@end

@cassilda: functions
│  Standard  functions  are  set in upright  (roman) type. Hyades  recognises the
│  usual names:
│  
│                            sin 𝑥     cos(𝑥)     tan 𝑥
│  
│                       arcsin(𝑥)     arccos 𝑥     arctan 𝑥
│  
│                                                   ⎛  𝑥  ⎞
│                        sinh 𝑥     cosh 𝑥     tanh ⎜ ─── ⎟
│                                                   ⎝  2  ⎠
│  
│                       log 𝑥     log  𝑥     ln 𝑥     exp(𝑥)
│                                    2
│  
│  Functions can take powers:
│  
│                                  2        2
│                               sin  𝑥 + cos  𝑥 = 1

% ─── CUSTOM FUNCTION NAMES ───────────────────────────────────────────────

@label fn_command
    For functions Hyades does not know about, \cmd{fn}
    (or the standard LaTeX \cmd{operatorname}) produces an
    upright function name:

    $$ \fn{softmax}\left(x_i\right) = \frac{e^{x_i}}{\sum_j e^{x_j}} $$
    $$ \operatorname{ReLU}(x) = \max(0, x) $$
    $$ \operatorname{Tr}(A) \quad \fn{Attention}(Q, K, V) $$
@end

@cassilda: fn_command
