% ─── SUMMATION ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@label sums
    \cmd{sum} draws the summation symbol.  Limits go in sub/super:

    $$ \sum_{i=1}^{n} x_i\quad
       \sum_{k=0}^{\infty} a_k $$

    \cmd{Sum}/\cmd{SUM} give larger variants:

    $$ \Sum_{i=1}^{n} x_i\quad
       \SUM_{i=1}^{n} x_i $$

    Tall bodies recursively maintain stable horizontal axes:

    $$ \sum_{k=1}^{n} \frac{\sqrt[3]{x^2+y^2}}{1+x} \quad
       \Sum^{n}_{k=1} \frac{\left(\frac{a+b}{c+d}\right)}{\sqrt{1+u^2}} \quad
       \SUM \frac{\sqrt{\frac{p+q}{r+s}}}{t} $$

    ASCII version:

    \setunicode{false}
    $$ \sum_{k=1}^{n} \frac{\sqrt[3]{x^2+y^2}}{1+x} \quad
       \Sum^{n}_{k=1} \frac{\left(\frac{a+b}{c+d}\right)}{\sqrt{1+u^2}} \quad
       \SUM \frac{\sqrt{\frac{p+q}{r+s}}}{t} $$

    \setunicode{true}
    Substantially unbalanced primary axis:
    
    $$ \sum_{k=1}^{n} \frac{1}{1+\sqrt{\,\int_{0}^{1} \frac{x^2}{1+x^2} \, dx\,}} \quad$$
@end

