% ─── INTEGRALS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@label integrals
    \cmd{int} draws an integral sign.  Limits go in sub/super:

    $$ \int f(x) \, dx\quad \int_a^b f(x) \, dx\quad \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} e^{-x^2} dx $$

    \cmd{Int}\cmd{INT} give taller variants:

    $$ \Int_a^b f(x) \, dx\quad  \INT_a^b f(x) \, dx $$

    More complicated examples:

    $$ \int_{0}^{1} \frac{x^2}{1+x^2} \, dx \quad
       \Int^{T} \frac{\sqrt{1+\frac{a}{b}}}{1+\sqrt{c}} \, dt \quad
       \INT \frac{\left(\frac{\sqrt{m}}{n}\right)}{1+q} \, dq $$

    Power rule:
    
    $$ \int x^n\,dx = \frac{x^{n+1}}{n+1} + C \quad (n \neq -1) $$
    $$ \int \frac{1}{x}\,dx = \ln|x| + C $$

    ASCII version:
    \setunicode{false}
    
    $$ \int x^n\,dx = \frac{x^{n+1}}{n+1} + C \quad (n \neq -1) $$
    $$ \int \frac{1}{x}\,dx = \ln|x| + C $$
@end

