% ─── LIMITS ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@label limits
    \cmd{lim} places its subscript directly below.  Other
    limit-style operators work the same way:

    $$ \lim_{x \to 0} \frac{\sin x}{x} = 1 $$
    $$ \lim_{n \to \infty} a_n $$
    $$ \max_{x \in [0,1]} f(x) $$
    $$ \min_{x} f(x) $$
    $$ \argmax_\theta L(\theta) $$

    Superior and inferior limits:

    $$ \limsup_{n \to \infty} a_n \quad \liminf_{n \to \infty} a_n $$

    L'Hopital:

    $$ \lim_{x \to a} \frac{f(x)}{g(x)} = \lim_{x \to a} \frac{f'(x)}{g'(x)} $$

    ASCII version:
    \setunicode{false}
    
    $$ \lim_{x \to a} \frac{f(x)}{g(x)} = \lim_{x \to a} \frac{f'(x)}{g'(x)} $$
@end

