% ─── LARGER MATRICES AND DOTS ────────────────────────────────────────────

@label matrices_advanced
    Larger matrices, identity matrix, and dot patterns:

    $$ \pmatrix{1 & 0 & 0 \\ 0 & 1 & 0 \\ 0 & 0 & 1} $$

    The general m-by-n matrix uses \cmd{cdots}, \cmd{vdots}, and \cmd{ddots}:

    $$ \pmatrix{a_{11} & \cdots & a_{1n} \\ \vdots & \ddots & \vdots \\ a_{m1} & \cdots & a_{mn}} $$

    Column and row vectors:

    $$ \pmatrix{x \\ y \\ z} \quad \pmatrix{x & y & z} $$
    
    Row breaks:
    $$ \matrix{ a & b ; c & d \\ e & f } $$
    
    Nested expressions in cells:
    $$ \bmatrix{ \frac{a}{b} & c \\ d & \sqrt{e} }\quad
       \pmatrix{ \sum_{i=1}^{n} i & \int_{0}^{1} x \, dx \\ \mathbf{A} & \mathbb{R} } $$
    $$ \bmatrix{ \alpha+\beta & \gamma \\ \delta & \epsilon\zeta } $$

    $$ \pmatrix{\frac{1}{2} & \sqrt{2} \\ \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2} & \frac{1}{2}} $$
    $$ A = \bmatrix{1 & 2 \\ 3 & 4} \quad \det(A) = \vmatrix{1 & 2 \\ 3 & 4} $$
    
    Tall entries:
    $$ \pmatrix{ \frac{a}{b} & x \\ y & \frac{c+d}{e+f} }\quad
       \bmatrix{ \sqrt{\frac{p}{q}} & r \\ s & \sqrt{t} } $$

    Nested matrices:
    $$ \pmatrix{ 1 & 0 \\ 0 & \bmatrix{ a & b \\ c & d } } $$

    Subscripts:
    $$ \bmatrix{ a_{11} & a_{12} & a_{13} & a_{14} \\ a_{21} & a_{22} & a_{23} & a_{24} \\ a_{31} & a_{32} & a_{33} & a_{34} } $$

    Spacing within cells:
    $$ \pmatrix{ xy & uv \\ pq & x\,y } $$

    Semicolon-only style:
    $$ \matrix{ a & b & c ; d & e & f ; g & h & i } $$
@end

