% ─── MATRICES WITH MATH ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

@label cases
    The cases command builds a piecewise definition with a left brace.
    & separates the expression from its condition:

    $$\fn{f}(x)=\cases{
        x & \text{if } x > 0 \\
        0 & \text{if } x = 0 \\
        -x & \text{if } x < 0
    }$$

    Cases work with complex expressions too:

    $$\fn{f}(x)=\cases{
        \frac{x^2 + 1}{x - 1} & \text{if } x \neq 1 \\
        \sqrt{\frac{a}{b}} & \text{otherwise}
    }$$

    
    Collatz function:
    $$f(n) = \cases{
      n/2 & \text{if } n \equiv 0 \pmod{2}, \\
      3n + 1 & \text{if } n \equiv 1 \pmod{2}\text{.}
    }$$
    
    Fibonacci sequence:
    $$F_n = \cases{
      0 & \text{if } n = 0 \\
      1 & \text{if } n = 1 \\
      F_{n-1} + F_{n-2} & \text{if } n > 1
    }$$
@end

@cassilda: cases
│  The cases command builds a piecewise definition with a left brace. & separates
│  the expression from its condition:
│  
│                                      ⎧  𝑥 if 𝑥 > 0
│                                      ⎪
│                               f(𝑥) = ⎨  0 if 𝑥 = 0
│                                      ⎪
│                                      ⎩ -𝑥 if 𝑥 < 0
│  
│  Cases work with complex expressions too:
│  
│                                  ⎧   2
│                                  ⎪  𝑥  + 1
│                                  ⎪ ──────── if 𝑥 ≠ 1
│                                  ⎪  𝑥 − 1
│                           f(𝑥) = ⎨
│                                  ⎪      ⎽⎽⎽
│                                  ⎪     ╱ 𝑎
│                                  ⎪    √ ─── otherwise
│                                  ⎩       𝑏
│  
│  Collatz function:
│  
│                               ⎧  𝑛 / 2 if 𝑛 ≡ 0 (mod 2),
│                        𝑓(𝑛) = ⎨
│                               ⎩ 3𝑛 + 1 if 𝑛 ≡ 1 (mod 2).
│  
│  Fibonacci sequence:
│  
│                              ⎧               0 if 𝑛 = 0
│                              ⎪
│                              ⎪               1 if 𝑛 = 1
│                         𝐹  = ⎨
│                          𝑛   ⎪ 𝐹      + 𝐹      if 𝑛 > 1
│                              ⎩  𝑛 − 1    𝑛 − 2

% ─── ALIGNED EQUATIONS ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

@label aligned
    The aligned environment aligns multiple equations at the
    & mark.  Double-backslash separates rows:

    $$\aligned{
        x &= c(a + b) \\
        \frac{x}{c} &= a+b \\
        -b + \frac{x}{c} &= a
    }$$

    Optional parameter configures the space around the anchor:

    \hcenter{\aligned[4]{
        x &= \sqrt{\frac{1}{2}} \\
        x &= y \\
        x^2 + y &= \sqrt{x^3} + 2y-y&
    }}
    
    Matrices in aligned:
    \center{\aligned{
        A &= \begin{pmatrix} 1 & 2 \\ 3 & 4 \end{pmatrix} \\
        \begin{bmatrix} a & b \\ c & d \end{bmatrix} &= B
    }}
@end

@cassilda: aligned
│  The   aligned   environment  aligns  multiple   equations  at  the   &   mark.
│  Double-backslash separates rows:
│  
│                                      𝑥 = 𝑐(𝑎 + 𝑏)
│  
│                                     𝑥
│                                    ─── = 𝑎 + 𝑏
│                                     𝑐
│  
│                                     𝑥
│                               -𝑏 + ─── = 𝑎
│                                     𝑐
│  
│  Optional parameter configures the space around the anchor:
│  
│                                              ⎽⎽⎽
│                                             ╱ 1
│                                 𝑥    =     √ ───
│                                               2
│  
│                                 𝑥    =    𝑦
│  
│                                              ⎽⎽
│                             2               ╱ 3
│                            𝑥  + 𝑦    =     √ 𝑥  + 2𝑦
│  
│  Matrices in aligned:
│  
│                                           ⎛  1    2  ⎞
│                                      𝐴 =  ⎜          ⎟
│                                           ⎝  3    4  ⎠
│  
│                           ⎡  𝑎    𝑏  ⎤
│                           ⎢          ⎥ = 𝐵
│                           ⎣  𝑐    𝑑  ⎦


% ─── ALIGNED INTEGRALS ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

@label aligned_integrals
    Integral formulas aligned:

    $$\aligned{
        \int_0^1 x^2 dx &= \frac{1}{3} \\
        \int_a^b f(x) dx &= F(b) - F(a) \\
        \oint \vec{B} \cdot d\vec{l} &= \mu_0 I
    }$$
@end

