% ─── INTERTEXT ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@label intertext
    Use \cmd{intertext} inside aligned to insert prose between
    equation rows.  It acts as an implicit row break:

    $$\aligned{
        x + y &= z \\
        \intertext{Substituting the definition of $z$,}
        x + y &= a + b
    }$$
@end

@cassilda: intertext
│  Use  \𝑖𝑛𝑡𝑒𝑟𝑡𝑒𝑥𝑡 inside aligned to insert prose between  equation rows. It acts
│  as an implicit row break:
│  
│                                  𝑥 + 𝑦 = 𝑧
│  
│  Substituting the definition of 𝑧,
│  
│                                  𝑥 + 𝑦 = 𝑎 + 𝑏

% ─── STYLE COMMANDS (NO-OPS) ─────────────────────────────────────────────

@label style_noops
    LaTeX math style commands are accepted but transparent, since
    Hyades has no math size concept.  This lets you paste LaTeX
    verbatim without errors:

    $$ \displaystyle\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \frac{1}{n^2} = \frac{\pi^2}{6} $$

    The commands \cmd{displaystyle}, \cmd{textstyle},
    \cmd{scriptstyle}, \cmd{scriptscriptstyle}, \cmd{notag},
    and \cmd{nonumber} are all silently ignored.
@end

@cassilda: style_noops
│  LaTeX math style  commands are accepted but  transparent, since Hyades  has no
│  math size concept. This lets you paste LaTeX verbatim without errors:
│  
│                                  ∞             2
│                                 ───    1      π
│                                 ╲     ──── = ────
│                                 ╱⎽⎽     2     6
│                                𝑛 = 1   𝑛
│  
│  The  commands  \𝑑𝑖𝑠𝑝𝑙𝑎𝑦𝑠𝑡𝑦𝑙𝑒,  \𝑡𝑒𝑥𝑡𝑠𝑡𝑦𝑙𝑒,  \𝑠𝑐𝑟𝑖𝑝𝑡𝑠𝑡𝑦𝑙𝑒,  \𝑠𝑐𝑟𝑖𝑝𝑡𝑠𝑐𝑟𝑖𝑝𝑡𝑠𝑡𝑦𝑙𝑒,
│  \𝑛𝑜𝑡𝑎𝑔, and \𝑛𝑜𝑛𝑢𝑚𝑏𝑒𝑟 are all silently ignored.

% ─── MATH INSIDE TEXT COMMANDS ───────────────────────────────────────────

@label math_in_text
    Inline math \textdollar...\textdollar inside \cmd{textit} or \cmd{textbf} is
    rendered as math (not styled as text).  The surrounding
    prose is styled, and the math appears in its normal form:

    \textit{Let $f(x) = x^2$ be a function on $\mathbb{R}$.}

    \textbf{We have $E = mc^2$ by relativity.}
@end

