% ─── ATOM-TYPE OVERRIDES ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

@label atom_type_overrides
    Override the default spacing category of a symbol.
    Analogous to TeX's \verb|{=}| idiom for suppressing
    operator spacing, but explicit:

    \cmd{mathord} -- suppress spacing (ordinary symbol):

    $$ a \mathord{=} b \quad\text{vs}\quad a = b $$
    $$ a \mathord{\leq} b \quad\text{vs}\quad a \leq b $$

    \cmd{mathrel} -- force relation spacing:

    $$ f \mathrel{:} A \to B \quad\text{vs}\quad f : A \to B $$

    \cmd{mathbin} -- force binary operator spacing:

    $$ a \mathbin{\triangle} b \quad\text{vs}\quad a \triangle b $$
@end

@cassilda: atom_type_overrides
│  Override  the  default spacing  category of a symbol.  Analogous to TeX’s  {=}
│  idiom for suppressing operator spacing, but explicit:
│  
│  \𝑚𝑎𝑡ℎ𝑜𝑟𝑑 – suppress spacing (ordinary symbol):
│  
│                                𝑎=𝑏    vs    𝑎 = 𝑏
│  
│                                𝑎≤𝑏    vs    𝑎 ≤ 𝑏
│  
│  \𝑚𝑎𝑡ℎ𝑟𝑒𝑙 – force relation spacing:
│  
│                           𝑓 : 𝐴 → 𝐵    vs    𝑓: 𝐴 → 𝐵
│  
│  \𝑚𝑎𝑡ℎ𝑏𝑖𝑛 – force binary operator spacing:
│  
│                                𝑎 △ 𝑏    vs    𝑎△𝑏

