│  
│                                   𝑎 +     + 𝑐

% ─── SMASH ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@label smash
    \cmd{smash} renders its content but collapses the height to
    a single line (the baseline row).  Useful to prevent tall
    content from stretching surrounding constructs like roots:

    Without smash -- the root grows to fit the exponent:

    $$ \sqrt{y^3} $$

    With smash -- the root stays compact:

    $$ \sqrt{\smash{y^3}} $$

    Smash on a fraction extracts just the bar:

    $$ \smash{\frac{a}{b}} $$
@end

@cassilda: smash
│  \𝑠𝑚𝑎𝑠ℎ renders its content but  collapses the height to a single line (the ba-
